The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to facility location, which is a classic topic in computer science and operations research. The use of local search techniques and approximation algorithms suggests that the paper belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-categories. The study of online and dynamic models also suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories, as these are areas where online and dynamic algorithms are commonly used. Finally, the use of metric spaces and embeddings suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category, as these concepts are relevant to the design of algorithms for robotic systems.
